  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Font Choices**\n\nI\'ve been analyzing the chosen fonts. \"Playfair Display\", the serif font, stands out due to its high contrast and distinct serifs, which lend a potentially dramatic flair. I\'m considering how this impacts the overall design aesthetic.\n\n\n**Refining Font Selection**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on font combinations that exude softness and professionalism, steering clear of anything that feels too aggressive or AI-generated. Considering serif fonts, I\'m exploring \"Lora\" for its balanced, contemporary feel, offering grace and warmth without sacrificing professionalism. \"Inter\" is a strong contender to replace \"Plus Jakarta Sans\" for a softer, more polished sans-serif. I\'m prioritizing readability and organic feel.\n\n\n**Evaluating Sans-Serif Options**\n\nI\'m now weighing the merits of various sans-serif fonts, like Manrope, DM Sans, and others, against existing choices. Manrope is particularly appealing for its modern, friendly curves and inherent softness. The goal is a clean, understated aesthetic. I\'m also analyzing what contributes to an \"AI\" aesthetic in typography, focusing on avoiding overly heavy weights, inappropriate italics, and excessive use of gradients or decorative text combinations. Readability and polish are key.\n\n\n**Implementing Font Hierarchy**\n\nI\'ve decided to implement a refined font hierarchy. I\'m now setting \"Lora\" as the serif font, appreciating its elegance and softness. For sans-serif, \"Inter\" is ideal, with its neutral, professional feel that doesn\'t resemble AI-generated designs. The CSS imports reflect these choices. I\'m checking existing components to see how to apply the new typography.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will look for combinations of fonts and stylized classes (like `font-serif` or decorative italics) across the project files using the grep command, so that we can soften them and achieve a highly elegant and human-crafted presentation."
